<TITLE> No pay rise for civil servants this month </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 4 (bdnews24.com)The civil servants are not getting a pay hike even this month. A secretary-level committee mandated to suggest ways to implement the seventh national pay commission recommendations for civil servants on July 1 finalised the recommendations. It proposed the implementation of the recommendations from July. Finance minister AMA Muhith said on Tuesday he would send the reports from the pay commission committee, defence committee and secretary committee to the cabinet after reviewing them. "The cabinet will give the final approval. But there is no possibility that the report will go to the cabinet this month," he told reporters after a meeting with visiting World Bank vice president for South Asia Isabel M Guerrero at the Secretariat. The committee recommended the lowest and highest pay scale at 1:9.45 but did not specify the amount. b
